<Docs title="Getting Started" description="Get Cloudcore CMS running locally in under 5 minutes.">
  <h1>Getting Started</h1>
  <p>Get Cloudcore CMS running locally in under 5 minutes.</p>

  <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Node.js</strong> 20+ and npm</li>
    <li><strong>Wrangler CLI</strong> — <code>npm install -g wrangler</code></li>
    <li>A <a href="https://dash.cloudflare.com/sign-up" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare account</a> (free tier is fine)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>1. Clone the CMS</h2>
  <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/cloudcore-cms/cloudcore-cms.git
cd cloudcore-cms
npm install</code></pre>

  <h2>2. Create the local database</h2>
  <pre><code>npx wrangler d1 migrations apply cloudcore-cms --local</code></pre>

  <h2>3. Start the API</h2>
  <pre><code>npm run dev:local
# API running at http://localhost:8787</code></pre>

  <h2>4. Start the admin UI</h2>
  <pre><code>cd admin
npm install
npm run dev
# Admin at http://localhost:5173</code></pre>

  <h2>5. Create your admin account</h2>
  <p>Open <a href="http://localhost:5173" target="_blank">http://localhost:5173</a> and create your first admin account. You're ready to create content.</p>

  <h2>6. Connect a frontend</h2>
  <p>Pick a <a href="/docs/frontends">starter frontend</a> (React, Next.js, or Astro), point it at <code>http://localhost:8787/api/v1</code>, and your content appears.</p>

